com.phunware.mapping.model

Class PwCoordinateSpace

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.phunware.mapping.model.PwCoordinateSpace
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public class PwCoordinateSpace
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    A PwCoordinateSpace is used to manage a dimensions for a map; such as width, height and scale. It is a simple bean type class; basic constructors and provides get/set methods for its properties.

      • convertX

        public float convertX(float x)
        Converts a x value from the map's coordinate space dimension to the map image's dimension. For example: If the coordinate space has a width of 100, and the image as a width of 500, converting an x value of 50 will return 250. A value of 39 will return 195.
        Parameters:
        x - Value to convert
        Returns:
        Converted value.
